 A^{T}P+PA=-Q
Q
A=\left[\begin{array}{cc} 0 & I_{n}\\ -K_{v} & -K_{p} \end{array}\right]_{2n\times2n}
K_{v}=k_{v}I_{n}
K_{p}=k_{p}I_{n}
I_n
n\times n
PA = (A^TP)^T
P
P_{ij}
i=1,2
j = 1,2
A^TP = \begin{bmatrix} 0 & -K_v \\ {\rm I}_n & -K_p \end{bmatrix} \begin{bmatrix} P_{11} & P_{12} \\ P_{12}^T & P_{22} \end{bmatrix} = \begin{bmatrix} -K_v P_{12}^T & -K_v P_{22} \\ P_{11} - K_p P_{12}^T & P_{12} - K_p P_{22} \end{bmatrix}.
-Q = A^TP + PA = A^TP + (A^TP)^T = \begin{bmatrix} -k_v (P_{12} + P_{12}^T) & P_{11} - k_p P_{12} - k_v P_{22} \\ P_{11} - k_p P_{12}^T - k_v P_{22} & P_{12} + P_{12}^T - 2k_p P_{22} \end{bmatrix}
